<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Bolgor:
[B]I'd have to agree alot with the idea that paying for spells (especially in in the 10k+ range) is something none of us should attempt to take part in. I've never bought a spell, though I'm 56 and still lacking MoK, Stun Command and Word of Vigor. My resoning is, that realy none of our cleric spells help US. Mark of Naltron or MoK or Aego doesn't make me a better solo-er... it makes me a better cleric. It benefits everyone else that I get my spells.

At the same time, I've never sold any spells. I have friends of every race and class, and everytime I get a new spell drop it goes to a friend of mine who can use it. On CT there was a brief span of time when 54 wizard familiars were going for 20k. I gave one to a guildie and one to a friend without a second thought. And they use them primarily to solo... I get no benefit from them.

It really urks me when someone tells me to MoK something, and I tell tehm I have no BP and haven't got the spell, to which they grumble and moan about how ill prepared I am and how I need to get my equipment and spell book in line.

And to the person who said that spells are a commodity like any other piece of equipment and should be treated as such... well, last I checked, me and every other class/race combo have the same number of inventory slots. I have to buy/camp/quest for enough items to fill all of those slots just as they do... then I still ahve a spellbook to fill. As well, if a player can buy a piece of equipment from another player, it also most likely means he can sell it when he's done with it. I cannot unscribe a spell and sell it when I upgrade, nor can i twink and alt with it, or pass it along to a guildie. If I buy a spell, that is money I'll NEVER see again.

Spells are set apart from other dropped items in the game. They're not the same type of commodity and their inflated selling prices abuse those classes that can use them. I for one may never have a complete spell book, but at least I'll never feel cheated after I empty my bank for a shield icon on page 5.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
